Diffusion

library(gifski)
n = 20
m <- matrix(nrow = n, ncol = n, data =seq(1,100)*0)

for(i in 1:5){
  for(j in 1:5){
    m[n/2 + i, n/2 + j] <- 1
  }
}
image(m)
# Animation
for(k in 1:100){
  col = 1
  row = 1
  for(i in m){
    if(row > 20){
      row = 1
      col = col + 1
    }
    
    if(i == 1){
      random = round(runif(1, 1, 5), 0)
      # Go up
      if(random == 1 & row > 1){
        if(m[row-1, col] != 1){
          m[row - 1, col] = 1
          m[row, col] = 0
        }
      }
      # Go right
      if(random == 2 & col < n){
        if(m[row, col+1] != 1){
          m[row, col+1] = 1
          m[row, col] = 0
        }
      }
      # Go down
      if(random == 3 & row < n){
        if(m[row+1, col] != 1){
          m[row+1, col] = 1
          m[row, col] = 0
        }
      }
      # Go left
      if(random == 4 & col > 1){
        if(m[row, col-1] != 1){
          m[row, col-1] = 1
          m[row, col] = 0
        }
      }
      # Stay
      if(random == 5){
      }
      
    }
    row = row + 1
  }
  image(m)
}
